JOHANNESBURG - eNCA's Ayanda Allie-Paine sat down with Hollywood actor Don Cheadle this week. He was in the country promoting the launch of the new Chivas Regal brand.He discussed his love of music, and his particular passion for jazz musician John Coltrane. Cheadle, who is a musician, said he doubts he would ever contemplate making an album. He noted it was something that might have been, but the amount of hours required to be a competent musician ruled out any likelihood of his making a career change.* View the attached video where Don Cheadle discusses movies, music and politics with eNCA's Ayanda-Allie Paine.eNCA